o=\r\nn) without initiation?\n\nFrom the Aghora books, I got the feeling that the n=\r\nature of the sadhanas \nmentioned in there absolutely required guidance for =\r\nthe sake of safety of the \nnative such as to prevent the native from insani=\r\nty or death. But ofcourse that \nwould be expected if one to a crematorium a=\r\nnd performs some sadhana only on the \nbasis of reading from some book or fr=\r\nom word of mouth.\n\nWhat I have read multiple times in Siva Purana is that i=\r\nnitiation is necessary \nfor quick results of sadhana, without initiation, d=\r\nesired results are either not \nachieved or takes a long time to acheive.\n\nW=\r\nhat is your take though on why initiation is important?\n\nThanks,\nBhupendra.=\r\n\n\n\n\n\n________________________________\nFrom: Dr Satya Prakash &lt;backtocosmicr=\r\noots@...&gt;\nTo: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com\nSent: Tue, October 26, =\r\n2010 10:07:15 PM\nSubject: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Translations, Initiation, Vedi=\r\nc vs Tantrik\n\n=C2=A0 \n\n\nNamaste friends,\n\nEssentially I agree with Narasimh=\r\na garu in most matters in this discussion. The \nonly major point where I di=\r\nsagree is whether one can do Sri Sri Chandi path \n*without initiation*. The=\r\n rest of the confusion on translation of mantras needs \nsome clarification =\r\nas there seems to be some unnecessary confusion. A few \npointers:\n\n1. There=\r\n are various sacred chants embedded within the Vedas, Puranas, Agamas \netc.=\r\n Broadly speaking such sacred chants can be categorised as mantras, stotras=\r\n, \nkavachas, dhyanams etc. Some stotras too are also treated as mahamantras=\r\n and \nmantras. The Samhita portion of the Vedas too is referred to as mantr=\r\nas.\n\n2. Undoubtedly mantras and stotras have to be chanted in the original.=\r\n Reading a \ntranslation is not even comparable to chanting the original cha=\r\nnt. So far it is \nfine.\n\n3. Whilst mantra, stotra and kavacha are all based=\r\n on Sabda/Vak, tradition makes \na distinction between them.\n\n4. As per the =\r\ntraditional view one doesn&#39;t need to be initiated to chant a \nstotra or dhy=\r\nanam. The case is not the same with most mantras. Mantras \ncontaining bijak=\r\nsharas, agamic mantras, mantras of Mahavidyas etc need \ninitiation. This is=\r\n the traditional view. Mantras from the Veda Samhita are not \nthe same as t=\r\nhese other mantras that need initiation, which are generally \nreferred to a=\r\ns Agamic/Tantrik mantras. Whatever you call these mantras the \nactual idea =\r\nis that these mantras are integral parts of larger and distinct \nspiritual =\r\nspecialities that need initiation, as in the case of Mahavidyas such \nas Ka=\r\nli or Sri.\n\n5. Vishnusahasranama, Sivasahasranama, Aditya hrdayam etc do no=\r\nt need initiation \nas they fall under stotra category only. Lalitasahasrana=\r\nma and Devi Mahatmyam \nare traditionally viewed not MERELY as stotras or pa=\r\nrts of puranas. They have a \nlarger status as integral parts of a Mahavidya=\r\n sadhana. Chanting them without \ninitiation is not recommended especially w=\r\nhen the reader combines the navarna or \nshodashi mantras too as an integral=\r\n part of the chanting.\n\n6. I know from personal interaction that acharyas b=\r\nelonging to both Kanchi as \nwell as Sringeri paramparas recommend initiatio=\r\nn for both the sadhanas of Sri \nSri Chandi and Sri Vidya along with their r=\r\nespective NAVAKSHARI AND \nSHODASAKSHARI mantras which are treated as an INT=\r\nEGRAL LIMB (ANGA) of the \nsadhana. Acharyas of both these traditions hold t=\r\nhat one needs to be initiated \nto chant the Navarna as well as shodashaksha=\r\nri mantras.\n\n7. Recapping my earlier stance, Devi Mahatmyam is a great text=\r\n that has an \nindependent status by itself as part of a Mahavidya. It is si=\r\nmultaneously a \nMahavidya, a Yogasastra as well as an Advaitic text in the =\r\nspirit of the \nUpanishads. ***As a Mahavidya the Navakshari is an integral =\r\npart of Sri Sri \nChandi path***. Thus tradition holds that one needs to be =\r\ninitiated to chant it. \nHowever if one wishes to benefit from the Yoga-Veda=\r\nnta or Sacred myth aspects of \nthe Devi Mahatmyam, , reading the sacred myt=\r\nh in the vernacular has been \nrecommended in my write-up, as chanting the o=\r\nriginal along with the navakshari \namounts to practicing the sadhana of a M=\r\nahavidya. In that case it is recommended \nto be initiated and go through th=\r\ne specialised sadhanas properly under guidance.\n\n8. Arguably if an uninitia=\r\nted person reads the Devi Mahatmyam in the original \nSanskrit as part of th=\r\ne *Pauranik* approach and not as a Mahavidya, it has an \ninherent problem i=\r\nn our times. The problem with attempting to do a parayana of \nDevi Mahatmya=\r\nm from texts alone (without initiation) is that most readers \ninadvertently=\r\n end up also chanting the Navarna mantra or stotras such as the \nSiddhakunj=\r\nika stotram which too contain the bijaksharas.\n\n9. I you carefully peruse m=\r\ny write-up on the Devi Mahatmyam, forget translating, \nnowhere do I put dow=\r\nn the Navarna mantra even in writing. Neither have I \nattempted to write a =\r\ncommentary on it. Translations of mantras do not have the \npower of the ori=\r\nginal mantra as Sabda or Vak. However it is recommended to know \nthe essenc=\r\ne or import (artha) of the mantra and its sadhana while chanting it. \nInfac=\r\nt `artha&#39; is the import, the essence of `Vak&#39;, not a translation! \n\n\n10. Fo=\r\nr those who are already doing Sri Sri Chandi path without initiation, \nther=\r\ne is no need to worry or be confused. There has to be a certain level of \ns=\r\namskara to be attracted to Sri Sri Chandi path itself. We all have it. \nOth=\r\nerwise we would not be doing it (initiation or no initiation). Please keep =\r\n\ndoing whatever you are doing. Just be cautious not to do sakama sadhana. A=\r\ns \nNarasimha garu has rightly pointed out it is better to just do the sadha=\r\nna \nWITHOUT asking for any favours or results. That attitude itself will re=\r\nduce a \nlot of the potential problem. Things will happen on their own accor=\r\nd in the \nnatural flow. Leave the rest to the compassionate Goddess. \n\n\nHop=\r\ne the above pointers help in clearing any confusion. \n\nRegards,\nSatya Praka=\r\nsh \n\n=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=\r\n=3D=3D=3D=3D\n\n--- In vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com, h ramalingam &lt;hramalinga=\r\nm@...&gt; wrote:\n&gt;\n&gt; Namaste everybody\n&gt; I want to share one anecdote happened=\r\n in front of Kanchi Maha Sannidanam Sri\n&gt; Sri Chandrasekara Bharathi Swamig=\r\nal\n&gt; When Swamigal was staying in a camp near Mysore in Karnataka One day a=\r\nll the\n&gt; learned persons male and female alike\n&gt; requested Swamigal to tran=\r\nslate Sri Vishnu SahasraNamam in kannada language\n&gt; so that they can chant =\r\nknowing the meaning fully.\n&gt; Swamigal didn&#39;t reply to this request which wa=\r\ns made early in the morning.\n&gt; Later in the day after the days pooja etc we=\r\nre over as usual Postman came to\n&gt; camp to deliver the posts came to Kanchi=\r\n Mutt Swamigal. Swamigal was\n&gt; seriously looking at the cover\n&gt; in front of=\r\n the learned members and was looking at one line written as PIN\n&gt; Code and =\r\nfollowed by six numbers. Then he asked the learned members to\n&gt; explain the=\r\n meaning of PIN Code and no one could tell that. But everyone\n&gt; understood =\r\nthe significance of that number. Then swamigal asked his crew\n&gt; member to p=\r\nick up one LIFCO&#39;s abbreviations book from his library and read\n&gt; the meani=\r\nng as POSTAL INDEX NUMBER and told the group that even the meaning\n&gt; of PIN=\r\nCode was not known to the group and still it serves the purpose and\n&gt; peopl=\r\ne are using it in day to day work. Similarly not knowing the meaning of\n&gt; V=\r\nishnu Sahar