 makes a distinction between\n them.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;4. As per the traditi=\r\nonal view one doesn&#39;t need to be initiated to chant a stotra or dhyanam. Th=\r\ne case is not the same with most mantras. Mantras containing bijaksharas, a=\r\ngamic mantras, mantras of Mahavidyas etc need initiation. This is the tradi=\r\ntional view. Mantras from the Veda Samhita are not the same as these other =\r\nmantras that need initiation, which are generally referred to as Agamic/Tan=\r\ntrik mantras. Whatever you call these mantras the actual idea is that these=\r\n mantras are integral parts of larger and distinct spiritual specialities t=\r\nhat need initiation, as in the case of Mahavidyas such as Kali or Sri.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;5. Vishnusahasranama, Sivasahasranama, Aditya hrdayam etc do not need in=\r\nitiation as they fall under stotra category only. Lalitasahasranama and Dev=\r\ni Mahatmyam are traditionally viewed not MERELY as stotras or parts of pura=\r\nnas. They have a larger status as integral parts of a Mahavidya sadhana. Ch=\r\nanting them without initiation is\n not recommended especially when the read=\r\ner combines the navarna or shodashi mantras too as an integral part of the =\r\nchanting.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;6. I know from personal interaction that acharyas belongin=\r\ng to both Kanchi as well as Sringeri paramparas recommend initiation for bo=\r\nth the sadhanas of Sri Sri Chandi and Sri Vidya along with their respective=\r\n NAVAKSHARI AND SHODASAKSHARI mantras which are treated as an INTEGRAL LIMB=\r\n (ANGA) of the sadhana. Acharyas of both these traditions hold that one nee=\r\nds to be initiated to chant the Navarna as well as shodashakshari mantras.&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;7. Recapping my earlier stance, Devi Mahatmyam is a great text that =\r\nhas an independent status by itself as part of a Mahavidya. It is simultane=\r\nously a Mahavidya, a Yogasastra as well as an Advaitic text in the spirit o=\r\nf the Upanishads. ***As a Mahavidya the Navakshari is an integral part of S=\r\nri Sri Chandi path***. Thus tradition holds that one needs to be initiated =\r\nto chant it. However if one\n wishes to benefit from the Yoga-Vedanta or Sac=\r\nred myth aspects of the Devi Mahatmyam, , reading the sacred myth in the ve=\r\nrnacular has been recommended in my write-up, as chanting the original alon=\r\ng with the navakshari amounts to practicing the sadhana of a Mahavidya. In =\r\nthat case it is recommended to be initiated and go through the specialised =\r\nsadhanas properly under guidance.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;8. Arguably if an uninitiated pers=\r\non reads the Devi Mahatmyam in the original Sanskrit as part of the *Pauran=\r\nik* approach and not as a Mahavidya, it has an inherent problem in our time=\r\ns. The problem with attempting to do a parayana of Devi Mahatmyam from text=\r\ns alone (without initiation) is that most readers inadvertently end up also=\r\n chanting the Navarna mantra or stotras such as the Siddhakunjika stotram w=\r\nhich too contain the bijaksharas.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;9. I you carefully peruse my write=\r\n-up on the Devi Mahatmyam, forget translating, nowhere do I put down the Na=\r\nvarna mantra even in\n writing. Neither have I attempted to write a commenta=\r\nry on it. Translations of mantras do not have the power of the original man=\r\ntra as Sabda or Vak. However it is recommended to know the essence or impor=\r\nt (artha) of the mantra and its sadhana while chanting it. Infact `artha&#39; i=\r\ns the import, the essence of `Vak&#39;, not a translation! &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;10. For thos=\r\ne who are already doing Sri Sri Chandi path without initiation, there is no=\r\n need to worry or be confused. There has to be a certain level of samskara =\r\nto be attracted to Sri Sri Chandi path itself. We all have it. Otherwise we=\r\n would not be doing it (initiation or no initiation). Please keep doing wha=\r\ntever you are doing. Just be cautious not to do sakama sadhana. As Narasimh=\r\na garu has rightly pointed out it is better to just do the sadhana WITHOUT =\r\nasking for any favours or results. That attitude itself will reduce a lot o=\r\nf the potential problem. Things will happen on their own accord in the natu=\r\nral flow.\n Leave the rest to the compassionate Goddess. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Hope the ab=\r\nove pointers help in clearing any confusion. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Regards,&lt;BR&gt;Satya Prak=\r\nash &lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=\r\n=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;--- In &lt;A href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogrou=\r\nps.com&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=3D_blank ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yah=\r\noogroups.com&quot;&gt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/A&gt;, h ramalingam &lt;hramalinga=\r\nm@...&gt; wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Namaste everybody&lt;BR&gt;&gt; I want to share =\r\none anecdote happened in front of Kanchi Maha Sannidanam Sri&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Sri Ch=\r\nandrasekara Bharathi Swamigal&lt;BR&gt;&gt; When Swamigal was staying in a camp n=\r\near Mysore in Karnataka One day all the&lt;BR&gt;&gt; learned persons male and fe=\r\nmale alike&lt;BR&gt;&gt; requested Swamigal to translate Sri Vishnu SahasraNamam =\r\nin kannada language&lt;BR&gt;&gt; so that they can chant knowing the meaning full=\r\ny.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Swamigal didn&#39;t reply to this request which was made early in th=\r\ne morning.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Later in the day after the days pooja etc were\n over as =\r\nusual Postman came to&lt;BR&gt;&gt; camp to deliver the posts came to Kanchi Mutt=\r\n Swamigal. Swamigal was&lt;BR&gt;&gt; seriously looking at the cover&lt;BR&gt;&gt; in f=\r\nront of the learned members and was looking at one line written as PIN&lt;BR&gt;&=\r\ngt; Code and followed by six numbers. Then he asked the learned members to&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;&gt; explain the meaning of PIN Code and no one could tell that. But eve=\r\nryone&lt;BR&gt;&gt; understood the significance o